    <stitle>HUBS, BEARINGS, AND SEALS (NON-DRIVE AXLES) - HUB ASSEMBLY - CAST SPOKE TYPE WHEEL STUD(S)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>CAST SPOKE TYPE WHEEL STUD(S)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>To replace wheel studs on cast spoke wheel, the wheel assembly does not have to be removed.</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove tire/rim. Refer to GROUP 17 - RIMS, WHEELS AND TIRES in the CTS-5000 Master
                    Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a stud extractor to remove broken stud. If stud is broken with very little of the
                    stud showing, the stud will have to be drilled and extracted using an easy out tool.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start stud into wheel hub spoke by hand.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start wheel nut onto stud until it is almost bottomed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start second nut onto stud and tighten (lock) with first nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn second nut with tool until stud bottoms into hub spoke.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Break two nuts loose and remove nuts.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
